# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Airalo Partners API (development)
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is gitignored.
#
# Docs: Request an OAuth access token from the Partners "Request access token"
# endpoint, then paste the bearer token below for local / Expo dev.
#
# SECURITY: EXPO_PUBLIC_* variables are embedded in the client bundle. For
# production, call Airalo from your backend only; never ship client_secret or
# long-lived partner tokens in a public app.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Option A — paste a bearer token from Postman / your backend (simplest for quick tests)
# EXPO_PUBLIC_AIRALO_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# Option B — OAuth client credentials (POST /v2/token). Token is cached in memory.
# ⚠️ EXPO_PUBLIC_* values are visible in the client bundle. Use only for local dev;
# production apps should obtain tokens on your server.
EXPO_PUBLIC_AIRALO_CLIENT_ID=
EXPO_PUBLIC_AIRALO_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Optional. Default: https://partners-api.airalo.com
# EXPO_PUBLIC_AIRALO_API_BASE_URL=https://partners-api.airalo.com
#
# Web + CORS: run the dev proxy in a second terminal, then point the app at it:
#   npm run airalo-proxy
# Default listen: http://localhost:8787
EXPO_PUBLIC_AIRALO_DEV_PROXY=http://localhost:8787
#
# Optional: Metro also tries to proxy /airalo-api (see metro.config.js); on many Expo web setups
# that returns 404, so the standalone proxy above is the reliable fix.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Webhook HMAC verification (server only — never bundle in the client)
# Used to validate `airalo-signature` on POST bodies from Airalo webhooks.
# Import verifyAiraloWebhookSignatureNode from lib/airalo/webhook-verify-node.ts
# in your Node server, or use verifyAiraloWebhookSignature in-app (less common).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AIRALO_WEBHOOK_API_SECRET=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: OAuth client credentials (for a Node/backend token exchange only).
# Do NOT use EXPO_PUBLIC_ for secrets. Implement POST "Request access token"
# on your server and keep client_secret server-side.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AIRALO_CLIENT_ID=
# AIRALO_CLIENT_SECRET=
